text: Carroll County is a county located in the state of New Hampshire, in the United States. As of the 2020 census, the population was 50,107, making it the third-least populous county in New Hampshire. The county seat is Ossipee. The county was founded in 1840 and named in honor of Charles Carroll of Carrollton, who had died in 1832, the last surviving signer of the United States Declaration of Independence. == References == Category:19th-century establishments in New Hampshire Category:1840 establishments in the United States Category:New Hampshire counties
title: Carroll County, New Hampshire
